2.00 hrs</TimeDiff><Notes>&lt;p&gt;During a full security review of &lt;strong&gt;chesleylawyers.com&lt;/strong&gt;, I discovered that the website had been compromised after an attacker used exposed Gmail credentials to inject hidden spam content across multiple pages, which negatively impacted SEO visibility, search rankings, and mobile performance. During the investigation I also found unauthorized modifications to plugins and theme files, broken contact and consultation forms caused by invalid ReCaptcha loading, and several broken scripts that were affecting mobile performance. In addition, Wordfence security scans were unable to complete properly due to outbound connection errors and skipped files. I immediately performed emergency cleanup and stabilization actions including removing all injected spam content, verifying and repairing plugins and themes, fixing the ReCaptcha issue so the contact forms work correctly, blocking the attacker&amp;rsquo;s IP addresses at the server level, updating the server security configuration (.htaccess), and resolving performance issues to restore proper functionality, security, and SEO visibility. During this process it was also discovered that the website&amp;rsquo;s master configuration file (&lt;strong&gt;wp-config.php&lt;/strong&gt;) had been shared in an unsecured communication channel, exposing sensitive credentials including the database password, database name and username, WordPress secret keys and salts, and the database table prefix, which could allow attackers to access or manipulate the site&amp;rsquo;s database or bypass login protections. Because of this exposure, these credentials must be changed immediately, including rotating the database password and replacing all WordPress security keys, and we request your permission to proceed with these updates or alternatively you can perform the changes yourself and confirm once completed.&lt;/p&gt;</Notes><Resource>P. Kumar
